author: HOWIE RUMBERG
title: Estrada, Blue Jays down Royals 7-1, send ALCS back to Kansas City for Game 6
text: Estrada, Blue Jays down Royals 7-1, send ALCS back to Kansas City for Game 6 Oct. 21, 2015 Updated 5:28 p.m. 1 of 20 Blue Jays starting pitcher Marco Estrada signals number one after being pulled from the game against the Kansas City Royals during the eighth inning. NATHAN DENETTE, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 20 The Blue Jays' Troy Tulowitzki hits a three-run RBI double off Royals pitcher Kelvin Herrera as catcher Salvador Perez looks on during the sixth inning. CHRIS YOUNG, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 20 The Blue Jays' Edwin Encarnacion (10) and Jose Bautista celebrate at home plate after scoring on a double by Troy Tulowitzki during the sixth inning of Wednesday's Game 5 against the Royals. NATHAN DENETTE, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 20 Royals center fielder Lorenzo Cain can't get a glove on an RBI double by the Blue Jays' Jose Bautista during the seventh inning. PAUL SANCYA, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 20 The Blue Jays' Chris Colabello, right, hits a solo home run in front of Royals catcher Salvador Perez during the second inning Wednesday. DARREN CALABRESE, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 20 Royals starting pitcher Edinson Volquez waits for the Blue Jays' Chris Colabello to round the bases after Colabello hit a solo home run in the second inning. JOHN SLEEZER, KANSAS CITY STAR/TNS 1 of 20 Blue Jays starting pitcher Marco Estrada throws to the Royals during the first inning in Game 5 Wednesday. NATHAN DENETTE, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 20 The Royals' Lorenzo Cain, right, reacts after striking out against the Blue Jays during the first inning in Game 5. MATT SLOCUM, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 20 The Royals' Mike Moustakas throws his helmet and walks away from home plate after striking out in the second inning against the Blue Jays during Game 5 on Wednesday. JOHN SLEEZER, KANSAS CITY STAR/TNS 1 of 20 Royals starting Edinson Volquez, right, stands off the mound as the Blue Jays' Chris Colabello rounds the bases following his solo home run during the second inning. DARREN CALABRESE, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 20 Royals starting pitcher Edinson Volquez reacts after loading the bases against the Blue Jays during the sixth inning. CHARLIE RIEDEL, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 20 The Blue Jays' Jose Bautista slides safely into first base as Royals first baseman Eric Hosmer misses the throw during the fourth inning in Game 5 on Wednesday. NATHAN DENETTE, THE CANADIAN PRESS VIA AP 1 of 20 The Blue Jays' Jose Bautista is safe at first past Royals first baseman Eric Hosmer during the fourth inning in Game 5. PAUL SANCYA, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 20 Blue Jays first baseman Chris Colabello flips over the outfield wall while unsuccessfully attempting to catch a fly ball hit by the Royals' Salvador Perez in the second inning. JILL TOYOSHIBA, KANSAS CITY STAR/TNS 1 of 20 Blue Jays first baseman Chris Colabello and fans try for a foul ball during the third inning in Game 5 against the Royals. PAUL SANCYA, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 20 The Blue Jays' Josh Donaldson gets hit by a pitch during the sixth inning in Game 5 against the Royals. CHARLIE RIEDEL, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 20 The Blue Jays' Josh Donaldson gets hit by a pitch during the sixth inning in Game 5 against the Royals. FRANK GUNN, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 20 Royals second baseman Ben Zobrist catches a line drive hit by the the Blue Jays' Dioner Navarro to end the second inning. JILL TOYOSHIBA, KANSAS CITY STAR/TNS 1 of 20 Royals pitcher Edinson Volquez fields a ground ball hit by the Blue Jays' Kevin Pillar during the fifth inning in Game 5. NATHAN DENETTE, THE CANADIAN PRESS VIA AP 1 of 20 The Royals' Alcides Escobar, top, leaps to turn a double play over the Blue Jays' Edwin Encarnacion during the fourth inning. DARREN CALABRESE, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS Blue Jays starting pitcher Marco Estrada signals number one after being pulled from the game against the Kansas City Royals during the eighth inning. NATHAN DENETTE, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS By HOWIE RUMBERG / THE ASSOCIATED PRESS
